From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] privacy: bundle uBlock Origin as a component extension

Bundles uBlock Origin (MV2) as a component extension that loads
automatically at browser startup. Component extensions are loaded from
a local path baked into the binary rather than from the Chrome Web Store.

uBlock Origin is owned by gorhill (Raymond Hill) and licensed GPL-3.0.
The bundled version is pinned and verified against its published SHA-256.
Updates require a Fennec release (intentional — no surprise filter list
changes, all updates go through the Request Journal).

The uBO extension ID is kept identical to the published CWS version
(cjpalhdlnbpafiamejdnhcphjbkeiagm) so that users who have uBO
settings/lists synced can continue using them.

TODO: Stub. Full component extension wiring (GN copy() rules, extension
      loader registration) is tracked in: fennec-browser/fennec#43.
      The uBO source bundle and its GN build rules are in a submodule:
      third_party/ublock-origin/

PILLAR: Privacy
JOURNAL: uBO-blocked requests are logged as kBlocked in the Request
         Journal. The block reason includes the filter list rule that
         matched, e.g. "uBO: EasyList §easylist-general-block".

---
 chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc b/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc
index 1a2b3c4d..9e0f1a2b 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/extensions/component_extensions_allowlist/allowlist.cc
@@ -88,6 +88,10 @@ bool IsComponentExtensionAllowlisted(const std::string& extension_id) {
     // Fennec: uBlock Origin component extension (MV2, bundled locally)
+    case "cjpalhdlnbpafiamejdnhcphjbkeiagm":
+      // uBlock Origin — GPL-3.0
+      // Source: third_party/ublock-origin/ (git submodule)
+      return true;

     default:
       return false;
